┌─ Summary ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                            │
│  An efficient implementation of combinatorial (un)ranking for sampling     │
│  elements from the general linear group over a finite field. The code      │
│  is written in C and rely on FLINT (Fast Library for Number Theory) for    │
│  field arithmetic and linear algebra operations.                           │
│                                                                            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─ Usage ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                            │
│  To run the test suite, issue the command `make test`. This will run a     │
│  series of randomized tests for the implemented algorithm.                 │
│                                                                            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
